# adherence_detector.tflite

Place your TFLite object-detection model here with the filename `adherence_detector.tflite`.

## Requirements

The model must be compatible with the **TFLite Task Vision ObjectDetector** API:
- Includes embedded metadata (TFLite Model Metadata Extractor standard)
- Input: single RGB image tensor, any size (the API handles resizing)
- Output: detected bounding boxes, class labels, and confidence scores
- Must contain at minimum the label classes: `"person"` and `"medical equipment"`
  (substring-matched, case-insensitive)

## Recommended models

- EfficientDet-Lite0 (fast, suitable for real-time analysis alongside VideoCapture)
- EfficientDet-Lite2 (higher accuracy if the device thermal budget allows)
- MobileNet SSD (lightest option for continuous frame analysis)

Custom-trained models for specific medical equipment can be exported from
TensorFlow / Vertex AI and converted to TFLite format using `tflite_convert`.

## Detection thresholds

See `AdherenceVisionAnalyzer.kt`:
- `SCORE_THRESHOLD = 0.50`  — per-frame confidence cut-off
- `MIN_DETECTION_RATIO = 0.60` — fraction of frames that must be verified
  for AUTO_APPROVED status
